# pbipandas
![CI](https://github.com/hoangdinh2710/pbipandas/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)
[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pbipandas.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/pbipandas/)

**pbipandas** is a powerful, modular Python client for the [Power BI REST API](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/rest/api/power-bi/) that helps you authenticate and retrieve data directly into **Pandas DataFrames**. 

âœ¨ **Now with modular architecture for better maintainability and targeted functionality!**

---

## ğŸš€ Features

- ğŸ—‚ï¸ **Comprehensive Metadata**: Get details for all Power BI items (datasets, dataflows, reports, refresh logs, datasources)
- ğŸ” **Easy Authentication**: OAuth2 authentication using client credentials
- ğŸ“Š **Pandas Integration**: Seamless integration with Pandas DataFrames
- ğŸ§© **Modular Design**: Use specific modules or the unified client
- ğŸ“š **Built-in Help**: Discover all functions with `client.info()`
- âš¡ **Bulk Operations**: Retrieve data across all workspaces efficiently
- ğŸ”„ **Refresh Management**: Trigger and monitor dataset/dataflow refreshes
- ğŸ“ **DAX Queries**: Execute DAX queries against datasets

---

## ğŸ“¦ Installation

```bash
pip install pbipandas
```

Or for development:

